article.headline: Colorado State 66, South Florida 65
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Matt Williams hit the first of two free throws with two seconds remaining to lift Colorado State past South Florida 66-65 on Monday night. Matt Nelson led Colorado State (6-4) with 17 points and added seven rebounds. Ronnie Clark scored all of his 10 points after the intermission to help the Rams complete a rally from a 14-point deficit. Williams finished with 11 points and nine rebounds. Terrance Leather paced South Florida (4-5) with 24 points and a career-high 15 rebounds. Bradley Mosley scored 14 points for the Bulls and Jimmy Baxter added 10. With the score tied at 65, Mosley missed a driving layup, and Williams grabbed the rebound. Marlyn Bryant fouled him in an attempt to regain possession for the Bulls, who have lost five of their past six games. Colorado State scored the first points of the game, but South Florida immediately answered with a 9-2 run. Later in the first half, the South Florida scored 11 consecutive points during a seven-minute span for its biggest lead at 23-9. Dwight Boatner hit a 3-pointer at the halftime buzzer as Colorado State cut the deficit to 31-23. The momentum carried over to the second half, when the Rams built a 10-point lead before the Bulls recovered down the stretch.
